author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Saturday's roundup | 4th-quarter TDs key as Norview edges Booker T.
text:
No. 6 Norview 30, Booker T. Washington 20 Darriel Mack and Kevin Marks scored fourth-quarter touchdowns to lift the visiting Pilots (4-2) past the Bookers (2-4).
Trailing 13-9 at halftime and 20-16 after three quarters, Mack scored from 1 yard out with 9:23 remaining in regulation.
Marks scored on a 34-yard TD rush with 1:44 left in the game.
Marks finished with 97 yards rushing and two scores, while Mack was 9 of 17 for 130 yards and threw for a touchdown.
Booker T. quarterback Alvonte Lawton threw a pair of first-half touchdown passes to Elanado Worsley and Andre Barnes III. Worsley's 15-yard scoring reception came on fourth and 13.
Key stats: N-Marks 18-97, 2 TDs rushing; Devon Watford 4-77, TD receiving; BTW-Lawton 9-21-1-158, 2 TDs passing.
- Reported by Jamaar Hawkins
____
Isle of Wight 60, Broadwater Academy 26
Bryce Casey tossed three touchdowns to three receivers and the visiting Chargers (5-1) pulled away from the Vikings.
Casey completed 10 of 14 passes for 133 yards and an interception. Will Morningstar, Chad McCann and Donald King had scoring receptions.
King and Morningstar added 127 combined yards on the ground, and each had a rushing TD.
Alec Edwards rushed for three touchdowns and 73 yards.
____
Trinity 59, Bishop Sullivan Catholic 14
Blake Bowen threw for 325 yards and four touchdowns and ran for another as the Titans (5-1) picked apart the Crusaders (1-4).
Bowen completed 13 of 18 passes, including two touchdowns to Trevion Armstrong.
Quinton Wingo ran for 78 yards and three scores for Trinity.
Bishop Sullivan quarterback Brandon Gaddy scored on a pair of 1-yard runs.
